    abstract  ="Crystals of difluorobromine() hexafluoroantimonate() are orthorhombic{,} space group {,} = 10·12{,} = 5·81{,} = 10·95 Å. The structure was refined by three dimensional least-squares methods{,} the final being 0·097 for 567 independent reflections. The bromine atom has two nearest fluorine neighbours at 1·69 Å{,} giving the expected angular ion{,} and two other neighbours at 2·29 Å{,} completing a much distorted square plane around bromine. These two atoms are part of the distorted octahedral co-ordination of the antimony atom and form bridges between the heavy atoms to complete an endless chain arrangement."
